gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Bulls 120, Bucks 113
gameRecap.excerpt: The Bulls defeated the Bucks, 120-113, in overtime and snap Milwaukees 3-game winning streak. Nikola Vucevic (29 points, 10 rebounds, six assists) and Coby White (23 points, seven assists, four rebounds) led Chicago as Zach LaVine and DeMar DeRozan missed tonights game. Giannis Antetokounmpo (26 points, 14 rebounds, five blocks, five assists), Brook Lopez (20 points, 6-10 3PT), and Damian Lillard (18 points, 13 assists, five rebounds) led the Bucks in the loss. The Bulls improve to 6-14 on year as the Bucks move to 13-6.
